The paper deals with natural language processing tasks and deep learning models for understanding mental health concepts derived from Cognitive Behavioural Therapy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of deep learning models, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with mental health concepts, which could make cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) relevant sub-categories.
